@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Hexarrow" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on an arrow, if it points toward an empty space
(small dot), it will move in that direction. However, if an arrow
or the game board edge blocks the way, the clicked arrow will
rotate clockwise by 60 degrees.

  If one or more arrows are in line and point toward the exit tile
and no arrow blocks the way, the arrows will go directly toward
the exit tile...

  As the game progresses, some tiles with a 'lightning bolt' icon
will appear from time to time. If an arrow moves on one of these
tiles, that arrow will be eliminated, as well as all neighbouring
arrows.

  You can restart the game any time, by clicking on the 'New Game' button.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

